"title": "8354: trustworthiness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8354: trustworthiness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>That quality of truthfulness and dependability which rewards faith. God is trustworthy and his people are called to be trustworthy in their dealings with other people. Scripture warns against pinning one's hopes on people and things that will prove untrustworthy.</p>\n<h2>God is trustworthy</h2>\n<h3>God's words are trustworthy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:28\">2SA 7:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7\">PSA 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:7\">PSA 111:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:45\">DAN 2:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15\">1TI 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:9-1Tim4:10\">1TI 4:9–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:5\">REV 21:5</a></p>\n<h3>God rewards trust in him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:4-Ps22:5\">PSA 22:4–22:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:6-Ps20:8\">PSA 20:6–20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:7\">PSA 21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:1\">PSA 125:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:9\">ISA 25:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a></p>\n<h2>Qualities of those who are trustworthy</h2>\n<h3>Integrity in business dealings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:36\">LEV 19:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:7\">HOS 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:11\">MIC 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>Honesty in handling money</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:15\">2KI 12:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:7\">2KI 22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:10-Luke16:12\">LUK 16:10–16:12</a></p>\n<h3>Not corrupted by greed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:21\">EXO 18:21</a></strong> <em>Qualities of the elders appointed by Moses.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:11\">PRO 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:18\">EZK 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:8\">1TI 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Ability to keep confidences</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:13\">PRO 11:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:19\">PRO 20:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:9\">PRO 25:9</a></p>\n<h3>Truthfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:17\">PRO 12:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:13\">PRO 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:16-Zech8:17\">ZEC 8:16–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15\">EPH 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:25\">EPH 4:25</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:17\">PRO 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:26\">PRO 24:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:13\">PRO 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:6\">PRO 27:6</a></p>\n<h3>Faithfulness with what is entrusted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:48\">LUK 12:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:27\">MAT 25:14–25:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:23\">LUK 19:12–19:23</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:1-1Cor4:2\">1CO 4:1–4:2</a></strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:17\">1CO 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20\">1TI 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Trustworthiness required in leaders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:2–5:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:11\">1TI 3:11</a> <em>trustworthiness also required in wives of deacons (NIV text) or deaconesses (NIV footnote)</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:7\">TIT 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people considered trustworthy</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:6\">GEN 39:6</a> <em>Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:7\">NUM 12:7</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam27:12\">1SA 27:12</a> <em>David. Though trusted by Achish, David was deceiving him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:5-2Kgs22:7\">2KI 22:5–22:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:10-2Chr34:12\">2CH 34:10–34:12</a> <em>those supervising work on the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:13\">NEH 13:13</a> <em>Nehemiah's treasurers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:4\">DAN 6:4</a> <em>Daniel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:20\">ACT 12:20</a> <em>Blastus, Herod's treasurer</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4\">1TH 2:4</a> <em>Paul, approved by God</em></p>\n<h2>People proving to be untrustworthy</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:22\">ISA 2:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5\">JER 17:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:15\">EZK 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Oneself</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:13\">PSA 49:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:26\">PRO 28:26</a></p>\n<h3>People in positions of power</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:3\">PSA 146:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa20:5\">ISA 20:5</a></p>\n<h3>Friends and family</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:10\">PSA 27:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:4\">JER 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:22\">JER 38:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:5\">MIC 7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Things proving to be untrustworthy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:31\">JOB 15:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:13-Job8:19\">JOB 8:13–8:19</a></p>\n<h3>Fortifications</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:52\">DEU 28:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:17\">JER 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>Military strength</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:7\">PSA 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:6\">PSA 44:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:22\">LUK 11:22</a></p>\n<h3>Wealth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:24\">JOB 31:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:7\">PSA 52:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:28\">PRO 11:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:7\">JER 48:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:15-Luke12:20\">LUK 12:15–12:20</a></p>\n<h3>Idols</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:17\">ISA 42:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:25\">JER 13:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18\">HAB 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Deceptive words</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:9\">PSA 5:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:4\">JER 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:8\">JER 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:15\">JER 28:15</a></p>",
